---
import Base from '../layouts/Base.astro';
---

<Base title="Services — Cody Smith" description="Web management, marketing strategy, training, and AI workflow advisory.">
  <!-- Hero -->
  <section class="relative pt-40 pb-24 px-6 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute top-0 right-0 w-[400px] h-[400px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-4xl mx-auto">
      <p class="reveal text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em] uppercase mb-8">Services</p>
      <h1 class="reveal font-serif text-5xl md:text-7xl text-neutral-100 leading-[1.05] mb-10">
        What I do and<br />
        <span class="gradient-text">how it's structured.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
        Everything runs on monthly retainers. No hourly billing surprises, no vague scopes. Each service has clear tiers — you pick the level of involvement that fits.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Web Management -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">01</span>
        <div class="gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <a href="/services/web-management" class="group">
            <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-3 group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300 inline-flex items-center gap-4">Web Management <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-all duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg></h2>
          </a>
          <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-8">Keep it running.</p>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="reveal">
              Your website is infrastructure. It needs hosting that isn't shared with a thousand other sites, security monitoring that catches problems before your customers do, and someone who actually reads the update logs before clicking "update all."
            </p>
            <p class="reveal">
              I manage WordPress sites on dedicated cloud hosting — my infrastructure, not some shared server you'll never have access to. That includes migrating your existing site over. Monthly site health reports show you exactly what happened, what's next, and what to watch. You never wonder if the work is getting done.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal">
          <div class="glow-card p-6">
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">Includes</p>
            <ul class="text-neutral-300 text-sm space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Managed cloud hosting
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Security monitoring & SSL
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Core, theme, and plugin updates
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Daily backups
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Uptime monitoring
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Site migration & onboarding
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Monthly Site Health Report
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Marketing Strategy -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 dot-grid">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">02</span>
        <div class="gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <a href="/services/marketing-strategy" class="group">
            <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-3 group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300 inline-flex items-center gap-4">Marketing Strategy <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-all duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg></h2>
          </a>
          <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-8">Decisions and priorities.</p>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="reveal">
              Strategy means telling you what to do, in what order, and why it matters more than the other twelve things competing for your attention. It means an SEO roadmap built on real keyword data, not guesswork. Competitive analysis that names names. Content briefs your writer can actually use.
            </p>
            <p class="reveal">
              I don't execute the marketing — I direct it. You get the plan, the priorities, and the reasoning. Monthly calls keep it on track. Quarterly reviews adjust the course.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 reveal">
          <div class="glow-card p-6">
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">Starts with</p>
            <p class="text-neutral-300 text-sm leading-relaxed mb-6">
              A strategic audit — a full read of your site, your market, and your competitors. The audit findings become your roadmap.
            </p>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-xs tracking-[0.15em] uppercase mb-4">Then delivers</p>
            <ul class="text-neutral-300 text-sm space-y-3">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Keyword research & strategy
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Competitive analysis
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Content briefs & direction
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Monthly strategy calls
              </li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3">
                <span class="text-amber-400 mt-1.5 text-[8px]">&#9670;</span>
                Quarterly reporting
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Implementation -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6 surface-1">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">03</span>
        <div class="gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <a href="/services/implementation" class="group">
        <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-3 group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300 inline-flex items-center gap-4">Implementation <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-all duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg></h2>
      </a>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-8">Changes to production systems.</p>
      <div class="reveal text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed max-w-3xl mb-12">
        <p>
          Some work doesn't fit a retainer. CRM integrations, analytics setup, landing page builds — these are projects with a start, a scope, and a finish line. I scope it, quote it, build it, and hand it over.
        </p>
      </div>
      <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-6 reveal-stagger">
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:0">
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-3">Integrations</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Form-to-CRM, analytics, email marketing, payment systems.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:1">
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-3">Page Builds</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Landing pages, service pages, content rewrites. Scoped and delivered.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:2">
          <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-3">Analytics Setup</h3>
          <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">GA4, Search Console, conversion tracking — configured and verified.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- Training -->
  <section class="py-28 px-6">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto">
      <div class="reveal flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
        <span class="text-amber-400 font-mono text-xs tracking-[0.2em]">04</span>
        <div class="gradient-divider flex-1"></div>
      </div>
      <div class="grid lg:grid-cols-5 gap-12 items-start">
        <div class="lg:col-span-3">
          <a href="/services/training" class="group">
            <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-3 group-hover:text-amber-400 transition-colors duration-300 inline-flex items-center gap-4">Training <svg class="w-8 h-8 text-neutral-700 group-hover:text-amber-400 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-all duration-300" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M17 8l4 4m0 0l-4 4m4-4H3" /></svg></h2>
          </a>
          <p class="reveal text-neutral-500 italic text-sm tracking-wide mb-8">Changes capability.</p>
          <div class="space-y-5 text-neutral-400 leading-relaxed">
            <p class="reveal">
              Training that works doesn't happen in a single afternoon webinar. It's a guided program — three sessions over three to four weeks, with real assignments between them. Your team practices on their own systems, makes real mistakes in a safe context, and builds actual skill.
            </p>
            <p class="reveal">
              I design training using the same learning science frameworks used in professional instructional design — not because it sounds impressive, but because it's the difference between a team that attended training and a team that can do the work.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="lg:col-span-2 space-y-6 reveal-stagger">
          <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:0">
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">WordPress & SEO</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Content management, basic SEO, site maintenance — so your team can handle the daily work confidently.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="reveal glow-card p-6" style="--i:1">
            <h3 class="text-neutral-100 font-medium mb-2">AI Workflows</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-500 text-sm leading-relaxed">Practical AI integration for your existing processes. Not hype — judgment. When to use it, when not to, and how to tell the difference.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- CTA -->
  <section class="relative py-32 px-6 surface-1 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute bottom-0 left-1/2 -translate-x-1/2 w-[500px] h-[300px] bg-amber-500/5 rounded-full blur-3xl pointer-events-none"></div>
    <div class="relative max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center">
      <h2 class="reveal font-serif text-3xl md:text-5xl text-neutral-100 mb-6">Want to talk specifics?</h2>
      <p class="reveal text-neutral-400 text-lg mb-10">Every engagement starts with a conversation about what you actually need — not a sales pitch.</p>
      <a href="/contact" class="reveal inline-flex items-center justify-center px-8 py-4 bg-amber-500 text-neutral-950 font-semibold text-sm rounded-lg hover:bg-amber-400 transition-all duration-300 hover:shadow-[0_0_30px_rgba(245,158,11,0.25)]">
        Start a conversation
      </a>
    </div>
  </section>
</Base>
